720698f-b.title: Manhattan: John Street - Nassau Street
720698f-b.text:
John Street, south side, west from (No. 48) but not including
William Street to but not including Broadway, showing in the foreground
the John Street M.E. Church (No. 44-46). Intersection shown on the right
is Nassau Street. The original edifice was erected on this site in 1768,
and rebuilt in 1817. The present building being erected in 1841.
May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
A 1imited view, showing Nos. 48, 46-44 (church), 42, and a part of
38-36. This view is as seen from Dutch Street.
May 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(3)
John Street,South Side,between Nassau and illiam Streets,showing  the John Street Methodist Episcopal Church.
